Good morning! For the attendance log, do we send that at the end of the bootcamp? and where exactly do we send it if we are supposed to?
column5:
We ask you to keep track of your attendance by using the attendance tracker located in the resources in Percipio and GitHub. This tracker should be manually updated each day by manually tracking every time you login or are logged out of the session. You then upload it only once when you request your certificate. You can access it from GitHub in the 5-Day Attendance and Certificates of Completion Info Video directory.

https://github.com/Skillsoft-Content/PMP5Day

The following link is where you will upload your attendance tracker when requesting your certificate after you complete the Bootcamp.

https://certificaterequest.skillsoft.com/

I didnt join 15 min earlier, did I miss something?
column5: Not much no. Just so you know, here are the attendance requirements for the 5-Day Bootcamp  – If you are unable to attend all the live sessions for whatever reason, you must attend at least 4 of the 5 live sessions and make up the missed session by watching the recording. A session is considered to be a missed session if you miss more than 15 mins (being logged out) of a session. If you miss more than 1 session, you would have to make up any additional sessions beyond the one by attending live in the next run for the 5-Day Bootcamp. You can't mix sessions between the 5-Day and 8-Day Bootcamp to get the 35 hours.

column2: I'm already certified... Is this bootcamp valid for PDUs required for pmp certification maintenace?
column5:
We are looking at getting it pre-approved. That said you can still self-report it after you chave completed the Bootcamp. Here are the steps.

1. Log into PMI.org
2. Click My PMI in the upper right hand corner
3. Select Dashboard
4. Select Report PDUs
5. Choose Course or Training
6. In the Provider field type Skillsoft and select 1008 Skillsoft
7. In the Course field type Course Name type in the following: PMP® Exam Prep: PMI (ATP) Bootcamp
8. Leave the description field blank
9. Put in the dates for the course. Your certificate will have the date completed
10. Use the following values for the PDUs claimed

Ways of working - 19.00
Power Skills - 8.00
Business Acumen - 8:00

11. Click to the checkbox to agree that the claim is accurate
12. Click Submit

Note: If proof is required you took the training, you can provide PMI with a copy of your certificate.

column2: I have a DASM certificantion from PMI, can this course contribute to my annual PDUs? How can I submit these?
column5:
We are looking at getting the Bootcamp pre-approved for PDUs; however, that hasn't happened yet. That being said, you can still self-report it using the following steps.

1. Log into PMI.org
2. Click My PMI in the upper right hand corner
3. Select Dashboard
4. Select Report PDUs
5. Choose Course or Training
6. In the Provider field type Skillsoft and select 1008 Skillsoft
7. In the Course field type Course Name type in the following: PMP® Exam Prep: PMI (ATP) Bootcamp
8. Leave the description field blank
9. Put in the dates for the course. Your certificate will have the date completed
10. Use may want to use the following values for the PDUs claimed

Ways of working - 7.00
Power Skills - 8.00
Business Acumen - 8:00

11. Click to the checkbox to agree that the claim is accurate
12. Click Submit

column2: Hi there, I had some issues getting into the class. Will this day count as me missing a session? Are you able to tell if I am considered absent for today?
column5: Here are the attendance requirements for the 5-Day Bootcamp  – If you are unable to attend all the live sessions for whatever reason, you must attend at least 4 of the 5 live sessions and make up the missed session by watching the recording. A session is considered to be a missed session if you miss more than 15 mins (being logged out) of a session. If you miss more than 1 session, you would have to make up any additional sessions beyond the one by attending live in the next run for the 5-Day Bootcamp. You can't mix sessions between the 5-Day and 8-Day Bootcamp to get the 35 hours.

column2: Test
Hi there, I had some issues getting into the class. Will this day count as me missing a session? Are you able to tell if I am considered absent for today?
column5: Here are the attendance requirements for the 5-Day Bootcamp  – If you are unable to attend all the live sessions for whatever reason, you must attend at least 4 of the 5 live sessions and make up the missed session by watching the recording. A session is considered to be a missed session if you miss more than 15 mins (being logged out) of a session. If you miss more than 1 session, you would have to make up any additional sessions beyond the one by attending live in the next run for the 5-Day Bootcamp. You can't mix sessions between the 5-Day and 8-Day Bootcamp to get the 35 hours.

I missed the first 20 minutes or so. Will I need to watch the recording of the first hour over to "complete" this session?
column5: Yes. you will need to watch the recording. Here are the attendance requirements for the 5-Day Bootcamp  – If you are unable to attend all the live sessions for whatever reason, you must attend at least 4 of the 5 live sessions and make up the missed session by watching the recording. A session is considered to be a missed session if you miss more than 15 mins (being logged out) of a session. If you miss more than 1 session, you would have to make up any additional sessions beyond the one by attending live in the next run for the 5-Day Bootcamp. You can't mix sessions between the 5-Day and 8-Day Bootcamp to get the 35 hours.

column2: How do I receive receive access to a practice exam simulator and mentors who are available to provide guidance and answer questions about the PMP® curriculum?
column5:
Check your learning portal

If you are a Percipio user, please follow these steps.

Step 1. Log into Percipio
Step 2. Select Library > Showcase > Skillsoft Bootcamps
Step 3. Choose Project Management Bootcamps
Step 4. Select the Project Management Professional (PMP) ATP Bootcamp: 5 Day Cohort channel
Step 5. Select the Practice tab and access the TestPrep exam.

For non-Percipio users try locating the TestPrep exam by searching your training site using the following title or ID.

Title: TestPrep: Project Management Professional (PMP) 2021 Update Aligned
ID: pm_pmp21_a01_tp_enus

If you have access to books in your training portal, check the Read tab from the same Bootcamp channel. If you are not on Percipio, but you have books, search for the book. The book is called.

PMP Project Management Professional Practice Tests: 2021 Exam Update, 2nd Edition
By: Kim Heldman
Publisher: Sybex © 2020

column2: Anyway to mute the chat? It becomes a bit overwhelming!!
column5:
If you are using the Zoom client click the upward facing carrot by that chat icon, click turn off chat previews

From the iPhone mobile app you can mute using these steps
1. Click the chat
2. Click the bell icon in the upper right hand corner
3. Select Mute

If you do not have the option to turn off previews or mute the chat, here are some suggestions to try:

- Open the chat window and push it off to the side and down, just leaving the title bar showing
- Keep that chat open and try not to pay attention to it, the popups will stop
- If you don't want to see the chat and have two monitors, you can pop-out the chat, put it on your second screen, and put another program in front of it

column2: I missed the first few minutes of this session that started at 10am ET and did not enter my name in the chat.  Do we still receive credit for our time by filling out the Attendance Tracker at the end of this course
column5: Yes, you still receive credit. Just be aware of the attendance requirements. Here are the attendance requirements for the 5-Day Bootcamp  – If you are unable to attend all the live sessions for whatever reason, you must attend at least 4 of the 5 live sessions and make up the missed session by watching the recording. A session is considered to be a missed session if you miss more than 15 mins (being logged out) of a session. If you miss more than 1 session, you would have to make up any additional sessions beyond the one by attending live in the next run for the 5-Day Bootcamp. You can't mix sessions between the 5-Day and 8-Day Bootcamp to get the 35 hours.

My internet dropped for a few minutes in the very beginning, does this count as missed session?? where can I confirm my attendance of today? Thanks.
column5:
There is no place to confrm your attendance. We ask everyone to manually keep track attendance by using the attendance tracker located in the resources in Percipio and GitHub. This tracker should be downloaded and manually updated each day by manually tracking every time you login or are logged out of the session. You then upload it only once when you request your certificate. You can access it from GitHub in the 5-Day Attendance and Certificates of Completion Info Video directory.

1. Click on the .docx file here.

https://github.com/Skillsoft-Content/PMP5Day/tree/main/5-Day%20Attendance%20and%20Certificates%20of%20Completion%20Info

2. Click the Download option on the fare right hand side.

3. Open the file and manually enter your attendance inormation each day.

4. Save the file.

5. The following link is where you will upload your attendance tracker when requesting your certificate after you complete the Bootcamp.

https://certificaterequest.skillsoft.com/

column2: I GOT DISCONNECTED FROM TRAINING FROM 10.00PM (EAT) - 10.30PM(EAT) DUE TO NETWORK ISSUE. HOW TO SORT THIS OUT NOW?
column5: Here are the attendance requirements for the 5-Day Bootcamp  – If you are unable to attend all the live sessions for whatever reason, you must attend at least 4 of the 5 live sessions and make up the missed session by watching the recording. A session is considered to be a missed session if you miss more than 15 mins (being logged out) of a session. If you miss more than 1 session, you would have to make up any additional sessions beyond the one by attending live in the next run for the 5-Day Bootcamp. You can't mix sessions between the 5-Day and 8-Day Bootcamp to get the 35 hours.

column2: test
Maybe it was covered but do you recommend getting PMBOK?
column5:
The Project Management Professional (PMP) exam is not written with one text or reference in mind, but rather is based on the following exam content outline

Exam Content Outline:
https://www.pmi.org/-/media/pmi/documents/public/pdf/certifications/project-management-professional-exam-outline.pdf

With the exam content as a roadmap, the PMP exam question writers may reference any of the books listed on the following web page and other texts not included in the reference list.

https://www.pmi.org/certifications/project-management-pmp/earn-the-pmp/pmp-exam-preparation/pmp-reference-list

Please note that A Guide to the Project Management Body of Knowledge (PMBOK® Guide) is one of the references listed. This may include both the Sixth Edition and Seventh Edition.

column2: Towards the end my session got expired and had to relogin. will it affect m 35 hours session requirement for PMP
column5: If you were disconnected for more than 15 mins for the entire day, then yes, it affeatcs your attendance. Here are the attendance requirements for the 5-Day Bootcamp  – If you are unable to attend all the live sessions for whatever reason, you must attend at least 4 of the 5 live sessions and make up the missed session by watching the recording. A session is considered to be a missed session if you miss more than 15 mins (being logged out) of a session. If you miss more than 1 session, you would have to make up any additional sessions beyond the one by attending live in the next run for the 5-Day Bootcamp. You can't mix sessions between the 5-Day and 8-Day Bootcamp to get the 35 hours.

For all other users try searching your Learning Portal using the key words 2021 Update

column2: Please share the link to the attendance tracker
column5:
You can access it from GitHub in the 5-Day Attendance and Certificates of Completion Info Video directory.

1. Click on the .docx file here.

https://github.com/Skillsoft-Content/PMP5Day/tree/main/5-Day%20Attendance%20and%20Certificates%20of%20Completion%20Info

2. Click the Download option on the fare right hand side.

3. Open the file and manually enter your attendance information each day.

4. Save the file.

5. The following link is where you will upload your attendance tracker when requesting your certificate after you complete the Bootcamp.

https://certificaterequest.skillsoft.com/

column2: How long is the course attendance valid for the certification?
column5: The training hours for PMP application purposes never expire once you achieve the 35 hours.

column2: I'm sorry, how do I log my attendance?
column5:
We ask everyone to manually keep track attendance by using the attendance tracker located in the resources in Percipio and GitHub. This tracker should be downloaded and manually updated each day by manually tracking every time you login or are logged out of the session. You then upload it only once when you request your certificate. You can access it from GitHub in the 5-Day Attendance and Certificates of Completion Info Video directory.

1. Click on the .docx file here.

https://github.com/Skillsoft-Content/PMP5Day/tree/main/5-Day%20Attendance%20and%20Certificates%20of%20Completion%20Info

2. Click the Download option on the far right hand side.

3. Open the file and manually enter your attendance information each day.

4. Save the file.

5. The following link is where you will upload your attendance tracker when requesting your certificate after you complete the Bootcamp.

https://certificaterequest.skillsoft.com/

column2: What is the learner kit, and how to get it?
column5:
Your training staff or HR Department for your company should be helping to facilitate the purchase of the learner kit by contacting your company's Skillsoft Account Executive who will provide them with your access key. If there is no process setup for them and they are asking you to purchase it on your own, you can start the purchase of the Learning kit from this web site by clicking on the Buy button. You will be redirected to another page to make the purchase.
 
https://www.skillsoft.com/pmp-voucher-offering
